PrefacePreface'Go Green' a series of books on Environmental Education (EVS) is based on 
the EVS syllabus as prescribed by the N.C.E.R.T according to NEP and NCF.
To enable the studen ts to realize their holistic potential in the process of 
learning, we have laid emphasis on the major skills that are to be 
develo ped through EVS. These skills include environmental sensitivit y i.e. 
awar eness, activity, projects, discussio ns scientific skills  and .
For the develo pment of these skills the learners need to be awar e of their 
surroundin gs and becom e keen observer . They should have the spirit of 
enquir y, be able to express their views and exhibit creativity and 
originalit y in doing activities and projects.
Keepin g these needs of t oday's lear ners in mind we ha ve prepared this 
series of EVS books.
These books will also enable the teachers to develo p the skills in studen ts 
as well as assess their learning process.
Any suggestio ns for the betterment of the book shall be thankf ully 
acknowledged and incorporated in the subsequen t editio ns.

Environmental Studies-3 06We all live in a family . A family is a group of people who are related to each 
other by birth or marriag e. People belonging to one family are called family 
member s.
People in a family
Member s of a family are related to each other in different ways. For example
! Parents of father are called paternal grandpar ents.
! Parents of mother are called maternal grandpar ents.
! Brother s and sisters of father and mother are called uncles and aunts.
! The childr en of uncles and aunts are called cousins.! How man y member s are 
ther e in this f amily?

Types of  families
Families may be of different types. Let us read about some of them.
1. Nuclear Family  Mother , father and their one or two childr en living together 
is called a nuclear family .LetsKNOW LetsKNOW

Similarities in a family
All childr en look like their parents in some way or the other . Some times, they may 
have similar nose or similar eyes or similar voices and so on. These are called 
hereditary features. They may be passed on to the childr en from both paternal or 
maternal side.
Every family has a family name which is called 'surname'. All 
members of a family write common surname.
What does the family teach us?
Mos t of the families have a set of customs and traditions that are passed from one 
gener ation to the other . Some common customs are
! Greeting elder s in the morning . 
! Praying daily .
! Having dinner together.
! Celebr ating special days and festivals together.
Our f amily is our fir st school bec ause it t eaches us man y things.  We learn v alues 
and good habits from our family .
In the family , we learn to care, shar e and help each other . Some good values that a 
family teaches are 
! Be polit e.
! Be respectful to elder s.
! Help each other A nuclear family is gener ally a small family .
2. Joint Family  Parents, grandpar ents, uncles, aunts and their childr en living 
together is called a joint family . A joint family is always a big family .

Our body parts help us in performing various functions like eating, walking , 
talking , hearing etc. Ther e are man y parts in our body and each part performs 
a special function. These parts are called organs.
Some of these parts like hands and feet can be seen from outside. But some 
parts like heart and lungs are inside our body and we cannot see them._____

Sense organs are an import ant set of external organs that help us to feel and sense 
the beautiful world around us. We have five sense organs. These are Eyes, Nose, 
Ears, Tongue and Skin.Sense OrgansThe body parts which can be seen form outside are called external body organs. 
Some examples are hands, legs, feet, mouth, eyes, nose etc.EXTERNAL BOD Y ORGANS
Eyes
Our eyes help us to see the beautiful world. With our 
eyes, we are able to iden tify things by seeing their 
size, shape and colour .
Our eyes are called windo ws to the world.
Nose
Our nose help s us to smell things. It tells us whe ther a 
smell is good or bad. We feel happ y when we pass by a 
flower-bed. But when pass by a garbag e dump, we 
wrinkle our nose.
The nose has two openings called nostrils, which help 
us to breathe.
Ther e are some hair presen t in our nose. They trap the 
dust and germs etc. and help us to breathe in clean air.
Ears
Our ears help us to hear different sounds. The sounds 
may be soft, pleasan t, loud and unpleasan t.
The unpleasan t sound is called noise.
Environmental Studies-313

Tongue
Our tongue help s us to taste. It help s us to know 
whe ther a thing is sweet, salty , sour or bitter.
It also help s us to chew and swallow food as well as to 
speak.
Skin
The skin is the largest sense organ. It covers our whole 
body . It help us to feel the senses of hot, cold, hard, 
smooth, soft, etc.
Taking Care of Sense Organs
We should take good care of our sense organs. Some of the ways are
! Wash your eyes with cold water, twice or thrice a day.
! Do not rub your eyes.
! Do not read in very brigh t or dim light.
! Never clean your ears with match stick or hair pin.
! Take bath every day.
INTERNAL BOD Y ORGANS
Let us talk about some body parts which are inside our body . They are not visible 
from outside and are called internal body organs.
e.g. Heart, lungs, brain and stomach.
Vitamin D is produced in our skin in the presence of sunlight. The skin also 
keeps us cool through sweating.You  Know Must 
Environmental Studies-3 14(Knowledge )

Heart
It is located inside our ches t. It pump s blood to 
all parts of our body .
Lungs
Ther e are two lungs presen t inside our ches t. The lungs 
help us in breathing.
The lungs absorb oxygen from the air we breath in.
Brain
Our brain lies inside our head. All body organs are 
connect ed to the br ain. The br ain c ontrols the functions of 
all other body parts.
Brain is called the master organ of our body .
Stomach
The stomach is a muscular , bag-lik e organ in our body . The 
main function of the stomach is to breakdown and digest 
the food that we eat.
Our heart is about the same size as our closed fist.You  Know Must 
You can't survive without a stoma ch.You  Know Must

cannot see, hear , speak or walk properly . These are people with special needs and 
are often called Differently-Abled people.PEOPLE WITH SPECIAL NEEDS

Our earth is full of wonderful things. When we look around us, we find man y 
things such as plan ts, animals, moun tains, birds, cars, buildings, humans etc. 
Some of these things are living while some are non-living.
Living things  are those which have life in them. For example plan ts, animals, 
birds, humans etc.
Non-living things  are those which do not have life in them. For example table, 
chair , building , stones, clothes etc.
Ther e are certain features that differentiate living things from non-living things. 
Some of them areCharacteristics of Living Things
Environmental Studies-319LetsKNOW LetsKNOW
